<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-19716] OOM when loading large uncompacted __consumer_offsets partitions with transactional workload</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-19716</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When loading a large poorly compacted __consumer_offsets partition with a transactional workload (alternating transaction offset commits and commit markers), we create and discard lots of TimelineHashMaps. These accumulate in the SnapshotRegistry&apos;s rollback mechanism. Overall, memory usage is linear in the size of the partition.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can commit the snapshot every N offsets in &lt;tt&gt;CoordinatorLoaderImpl&lt;/tt&gt;, to allow the memory to be reclaimed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
